title: PML-N’s Bilal Azhar Kiani wins NA-60 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz’ (PML-N) Candidate Bilal Azhar Kiani has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-60 Jhelum-I by securing 99,948 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate Hassan Adeel, who bagged 90,474 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.08 percent.
